      "content": "You are absolutely overthinking the risk; ibuprofen at 200mg is a standard, low dose that is perfectly safe for most people, but for someone with chronic kidney disease, even a single 200mg dose can cause an acute spike in blood pressure and strain the kidneys. Since you already took one, you need to stop taking it immediately and contact your doctor right away to have them monitor your kidney function and adjust your medication plan. Do not wait for symptoms to change, as kidney damage can happen quickly and silently.",
